Items.Description:
I was instructed by Andrey to run a query to show database table size using

Â 

SELECT Â 
Â  t.NAME AS TableName,Â 
Â  s.Name AS SchemaName,Â 
Â  p.rows AS RowCounts,Â 
Â  SUM(a.total_pages) * 8 AS TotalSpaceKB, Â 
Â  SUM(a.used_pages) * 8 AS UsedSpaceKB, Â 
Â  (SUM(a.total_pages) - SUM(a.used_pages)) * 8 AS UnusedSpaceKBÂ 
FROM Â 
Â  sys.tables tÂ 
INNER JOIN Â  Â  Â Â 
Â  sys.indexes i ON t.OBJECT_ID = i.object_idÂ 
INNER JOIN Â 
Â  sys.partitions p ON i.object_id = p.OBJECT_ID AND i.index_id = p.index_idÂ 
INNER JOIN Â 
Â  sys.allocation_units a ON p.partition_id = a.container_idÂ 
LEFT OUTER JOIN Â 
Â  sys.schemas s ON t.schema_id = s.schema_idÂ 
WHERE Â 
Â  t.NAME NOT LIKE 'dt%' Â 
Â  AND t.is_ms_shipped = 0Â 
Â  AND i.OBJECT_ID > 255 Â 
GROUP BY Â 
Â  t.Name, s.Name, p.RowsÂ 
ORDER BY Â 
Â  TotalSpaceKB desc
